programme.title: Silver Linings
programme.desc: Jessy Nelson, a lifelong rider, was rising to the top of his career when a crash left him paralysed. Today he's still a racer, just not on two wheels.

programme.title: Forced Perspective
programme.sub-title: The story of artist Derek Hess
programme.desc: Walking the tightrope between creativity and mental illness has given life to artist Derek Hess’s work. Artist Derek Hess’s journey includes alcoholism and bipolar disorder, but these demons have inspired emotionally evocative work that hangs in renowned galleries such as the Louvre in Paris.

programme.title: Moto 8: The Movie
programme.desc: The motocross bar is raised again as the greatest riders in the game explore the world’s most epic locations. From the biggest motocross tracks on Earth to the off-road wonderscape of the Australian Outback, Moto 8: The Movie pairs the greatest riders in the game and the world’s most breathtaking locations.

programme.title: The current state of jazz... London
programme.desc: London is seeing a burgeoning and globally respected jazz scene like never before. The birthplace of countless musical genres, London has always been a hub of boundary-pushing creativity. Never before, however, has the UK's capital seen such a burgeoning and globally respected jazz scene as it’s currently enjoying.

programme.title: Hanging Spear
programme.desc: World class whitewater kayakers Steve Fisher and Pat Keller explore the Hanging Spear Gorge. Join world class whitewater kayakers Steve Fisher and Pat Keller as they explore the Hanging Spear Gorge of the Opalescent River, the highest source of the Hudson and the deepest part of New York State’s High Peaks wilderness.

programme.title: Algo Está Pasando
programme.desc: Discover the story behind the people who took rap into a country ruled by a political dictatorship. Take a journey through 30 years of history and get a glimpse into the story behind the people who, despite limited resources, took rap into a country ruled by a political dictatorship.

programme.title: Chasing Niagara
programme.sub-title: Every dream has a point of no return
programme.desc: Follow pro kayaker Rafa Ortiz’s journey in pursuit of his dream to paddle over North America’s Niagara Falls. When pro kayaker Rafa Ortiz decides to chase his dream to paddle over North America’s Niagara Falls, he can't imagine the journey to get there. As he and his friends prepare for their adventure, they realise the path may have a mind of its own.

programme.title: Crossing Corsica
programme.desc: Ultrarunner François d’Haene attempts to break the record for running the 180km GR20 trail. French ultrarunner and winemaker François d’Haene attempts to cross Corsica from north to south along the legendary 180km-long GR20 mountain trail in world record-breaking time – under 31 hours and 6 minutes.

programme.title: How to approach a line
programme.desc: Queen B takes the opportunity to see how other drifters approach their lines. With only four weeks to go before the DriftCup competition Queen B takes the opportunity to go to Scotland and find out how other drifters approach their lines.

programme.title: Put your game face on
programme.desc: Queen B meets up with Jojo Sharp at Scotland's Driftland to walk through the track and plan the drive. Queen B meets up with Jojo Sharp at Driftland, in Fife, Scotland, to walk through the track and plan the drive. Once it's planned, it's time to test drive and find the edges.

programme.title: Anna Gasser
programme.desc: Find out a few things about the Austrian snowboarder’s thoughts and feelings on her chosen sport. The Austrian snowboarder shares her earliest experiences of boarding on the slopes, the achievements she’s proud of, who and what inspires her and why she loves her chosen sport so much.

programme.title: Marcus Kleveland
programme.desc: Get to know one of the most progressive snowboarders on the planet – a teenager with the world at his feet. Get to know one of the most progressive snowboarders on the planet: Marcus Kleveland.
